data.title: Charles C Mann-7
data.meta_description:
Photos taken during a lecture by best selling author Charles C. Mann. Mann, who wrote "1491" and "1493" argues that the Western assimilation of potatoes, yams and the near eradication of Native Americans has had long-lasting effects on the entire globe, from floods in China to the Irish Potato Famine of the early 19th Century.
	
	Dean Cynthia Weick introduces Mann.
data.text:
Photos taken during a lecture by best selling author Charles C. Mann. Mann, who wrote "1491" and "1493" argues that the Western assimilation of potatoes, yams and the near eradication of Native Americans has had long-lasting effects on the entire globe, from floods in China to the Irish Potato Famine of the early 19th Century.

Dean Cynthia Weick introduces Mann.
